Philip,

I've been working on getting a Canadian domain registered, together
with a small group of people representing DRE, NetNorth, and the
Canadian arm of UUCP. We're having difficulty trying to come to an
agreement on what the domain name and second-level domain names should
be, although I think that CA is going to win out, with organization
names at the second level. This is because it fits the RFC920
recommendations, and because it will likely fit the CCITT/ISO directory
service recommendations when they come out. (Actually CCITT/ISO also
talks about geographic "locales", so we will probably see provinces
appear eventually, and cities too, with the possibility of organization
names at each level.)

If your information runs counter to this, or if you know of a separate
group trying to register a Canadian domain, please let me know.

Regards,
John Demco

